But in the corners, you could at least behave like a bus driver.

430
00:27:45,185 --> 00:27:48,104
我把保时捷挡在线路之外
I've shut the door on the Porsche.

431
00:27:48,105 --> 00:27:50,905
你那小身板在这里没用！
Your Oyster card is about to expire!

432
00:27:58,225 --> 00:28:00,065
冲线！
And across the line!

433
00:28:01,345 --> 00:28:03,265
谢谢
Thank you.

434
00:28:06,385 --> 00:28:10,865
我从没在赛道上跑得这么欢
I have never enjoyed my time on a race track as much as that.

435
00:28:13,345 --> 00:28:18,984
实际上，我在这车里的一整天都很享受。当然也有些缺点
In fact, I enjoyed my whole day with the bus. There are a few drawbacks.

436
00:28:18,985 --> 00:28:21,584
比如停车，油耗，倒车等等
Parking,fuel consumption, reversing,

437
00:28:21,585 --> 00:28:25,064
但同样的问题也困扰着像布加迪威龙这样的超级跑车
but all that is true of the Bugatti Veyron, as well.

438
00:28:25,065 --> 00:28:28,864
好的方面，这车很宽敞，很有个性
On the plus side,it's roomy, it's distinctive,

439
00:28:28,865 --> 00:28:31,105
驾驶感也很出色
and it's extremely nice to drive.

440
00:28:33,825 --> 00:28:37,185
所有这一切，都使它堪称一辆超级巴士
All in all,I think it would make a super car.

441
00:28:43,865 --> 00:28:46,824
等等
Hang on.

442
00:28:46,825 --> 00:28:49,864
等等。什么？
Hang on a minute. What?

443
00:28:49,865 --> 00:28:53,744
你是不是五感尽失了？
Have you completely taken leave of your senses?

444
00:28:53,745 --> 00:28:58,544
你说这家伙是这家伙的替代者？
Are you seriously proposing THIS as an alternative to THIS?

445
00:28:58,545 --> 00:29:03,344
不，这么看，哈蒙德，听我说。艾伦·休格(英国的亿万富翁),他是个富豪
No, look, Hammond, let me explain.Lord Sir Sugar, he is a wealthy man,

446
00:29:03,345 --> 00:29:07,264
但他对0-60英里加速两秒以内的事情没兴趣，对吧？
but he's not interested in doing nought to 60 in two seconds, is he?

447
00:29:07,265 --> 00:29:10,784
如果他有一辆这车，他就能招待好他的小伙伴们
If he had one of these,he could take all his mates, well,

448
00:29:10,785 --> 00:29:12,984
如果他有小伙伴的话，并且度过愉快的一天
if he's got any,and have a lovely day out.

449
00:29:12,985 --> 00:29:14,904
这很难证实，对吧？
It's hardly practical, is it?

450
00:29:14,905 --> 00:29:18,664
不，哈蒙德，我认为梅说明了一件事。噢，看在上帝的份上...
No, Hammond, I think he's onto something. Oh, for God's sake...

451
00:29:18,665 --> 00:29:20,904
不，不，如果你想要一辆雷克萨斯LFA
No, no, because if you wanted a Lexus LFA,

452
00:29:20,905 --> 00:29:23,624
但你又是一个计划生育政策的反对者
but you'd had a papal attitude to birth control -

453
00:29:23,625 --> 00:29:26,865
换言之你有很多孩子 - 这就是你的不二选择
a lot of children - this is ideal.

454
00:29:26,985 --> 00:29:29,064
没错。你也不用自己开车
Exactly right.And you don't have to drive,

455
00:29:29,065 --> 00:29:31,144
你能找个人为你开车
you could get somebody to drive it for you.

456
00:29:31,145 --> 00:29:33,304
我们通常把这人叫做，我不知道该怎么说，公交司机。
You could call him the,I don't know, the bus driver.

457
00:29:33,305 --> 00:29:36,504
噢，搞什么名堂！等等，这个主意怎么样？
Oh, for crying out loud!Hang on, how's this for an idea?

458
00:29:36,505 --> 00:29:39,424
你等地方政府买下这车
You get the local authority to buy the bus

459
00:29:39,425 --> 00:29:42,904
然后你就可以乘坐它了,你唯一要做的只是每次上车刷卡而已
and then you can just use it now and then in return for a small fee.

460
00:29:42,905 --> 00:29:45,704
不，詹姆斯，那就变成共产主义了
No, James, that would be communism.

461
00:29:45,705 --> 00:29:49,504
总之，现在又到了我们的明星驾驶廉价车环节
Anyway, it's time now to put a star in our reasonably-priced car.

462
00:29:49,505 --> 00:29:52,944
今晚我的嘉宾是一个住在英国的澳洲人
Now, my guest tonight is an Australian who lives in Britain,

463
00:29:52,945 --> 00:29:55,744
但不寻常的是，他不在酒吧工作
but, unusually,he doesn't work in a pub.

464
00:29:55,745 --> 00:29:59,344
相反,他的工作是在
Instead, he works in the marketing department

465
00:29:59,345 --> 00:30:03,984
一家大型能量饮料制造公司的营销部门，并且刚刚提交了辞职信
of a large energy drinks company and he's just handed his notice in.

466
00:30:03,985 --> 00:30:06,465
女士们先生们，欢迎马克韦伯
Ladies and gentlemen,please welcome Mark Webber.

467
00:30:11,065 --> 00:30:12,584
马克韦伯！
Mark Webber!

468
00:30:12,585 --> 00:30:14,225
你好吗？
How are you?

469
00:30:17,865 --> 00:30:21,784
请坐。请坐
Have a seat. Have a seat.

470
00:30:21,785 --> 00:30:25,624
最受欢迎的人物，我说过，在F1围场内
One of the most popular figures,I say, in Formula 1.

471
00:30:25,625 --> 00:30:28,104
我们有如此多的相似处
Now, we have so much in common.

472
00:30:28,105 --> 00:30:34,544
我们有相同的体重，我了解的。你们笑啥？
We have the same body fat index,I know that. Why are you laughing?

473
00:30:34,545 --> 00:30:36,904
一模一样。但最主要的是我们有共同之处
Exactly the same. But the main thing we have in common,

474
00:30:36,905 --> 00:30:39,824
除了相同的体重
apart from the same body fat index,

475
00:30:39,825 --> 00:30:43,624
还有爱好骑单车
is cycling.

476
00:30:43,625 --> 00:30:45,504
我现在是个骑自行车的人
I'm now a cyclist.

477
00:30:45,505 --> 00:30:48,344
我听说这是你的新爱好
I hear it's a new passion for you.

478
00:30:48,345 --> 00:30:50,984
而你，当然，所有人都知道你是个单车运动员
And you, of course,are well-known as a cyclist.

479
00:30:50,985 --> 00:30:54,544
你参加了很多比赛。我今年也参加了几次比赛
You do a lot of competing. I've done a little bit over the years.

480
00:30:54,545 --> 00:30:56,744
有人说你是最合适的车手
Somebody said you are the fittest driver.

481
00:30:56,745 --> 00:30:59,304
我有合适的体型。我认为所有的人都适合。
I'm in reasonable shape.I think all the guys are fit now.

482
00:30:59,305 --> 00:31:01,384
如果你是最合适的F1车手
If you're the fittest Formula 1 driver,

483
00:31:01,385 --> 00:31:03,824
你就是这个世界上所有运动的最合适运动员
you've got to be one of the fittest athletes.

484
00:31:03,825 --> 00:31:07,344
如果我们做了很多不同的尝试,我想,是这么回事
If we did lots and lots of different challenges, I think, yeah.

485
00:31:07,345 --> 00:31:10,584
那样真不错。你可以试试不同的运动
That would be good.Let's get you all playing all the different sports.

486
00:31:10,585 --> 00:31:11,944
你玩足球吗？欧洲足球还是你们澳洲那种愚蠢的足球？
Do you play football?Ours or your silly football?

487
00:31:11,945 --> 00:31:13,704
不要聊狮子巡回赛（橄榄球赛事，四年一届）
We won't get onto the Lions and Australia.

488
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:15,584
说点别的
We'll leave that well alone.

489
00:31:15,585 --> 00:31:19,184
这里有了解的人。有人知道你说的是什么
Somebody's here. Somebody understands what you're on about.

490
00:31:19,185 --> 00:31:21,705
狮子队和小袋鼠队，我们很喜欢这两支队伍
Lions and Wallabies,we really enjoyed that.

491
00:31:23,345 --> 00:31:24,305
还有灰烬杯（灰烬杯板球赛，英国和澳洲之间的世界板球顶级赛事）
And the Ashes.

492
00:31:26,265 --> 00:31:29,584
你一定很喜欢住在这里的这最后几年
You must have really enjoyed living here these last few years.

493
00:31:29,585 --> 00:31:32,024
我认为上届灰烬杯很精彩
I thought the previous Ashes was quite a good series.

494
00:31:32,025 --> 00:31:35,105
我的意思是,英国队的南非裔球员表现的很好
I mean, all the South Africans played well for you guys.

495
00:31:37,025 --> 00:31:40,264
你骑车的总里程数有多少了？骑车？
So how much mileage have you done on the bike? On the bike?

496
00:31:40,265 --> 00:31:42,664
我已经骑了...三
I've done... three.

497
00:31:42,665 --> 00:31:44,544
3英里（4.8公里）
Three miles.

498
00:31:44,545 --> 00:31:47,344
我对单车运动有一点要说明，这是个，这么说吧
One thing I will say about cycling is, it is, well,

499
00:31:47,345 --> 00:31:49,424
这是一项很危险的运动
it's pretty dangerous.

500
00:31:49,425 --> 00:31:53,384
这么多年来，你也有过很多次赛道事故，是这样吧
Over the years, you've had a number of car accidents, let's be honest.

501
00:31:53,385 --> 00:31:55,024
如果你参加比赛，你就会遇上撞车
If you race cars, you'll crash cars.

502
00:31:55,025 --> 00:31:57,664
我们有张事故照片。是勒芒24小时耐力赛的一次事故
We've got a photograph of a crash.I believe it was at Le Mans.

503
00:31:57,665 --> 00:32:01,104
一张静态照片。没错，这就是你以前驾驶的奔驰赛车
A still photo.Yeah, this is you in a Mercedes.

504
00:32:01,105 --> 00:32:05,025
我刚说赛车事故，这看起来实际上是场空难。当时怎么回事？
I say car crash, that is a plane crash going on. How did that happen?

505
00:32:06,065 --> 00:32:09,424
实际上，在那条赛道上，90年代末期，那些赛车安全性很糟糕
Actually, in that era, the late 90s,the cars were super unsafe,

506
00:32:09,425 --> 00:32:12,304
所以很多赛车都飞起来过。这是常事
so a lot of cars were flying.Just the regulations.

507
00:32:12,305 --> 00:32:14,224
所以当时你在那辆车里，想些什么...?
So you're sitting in there,thinking...?

508
00:32:14,225 --> 00:32:17,624
我当时想，显然我失去控制了
I'm thinking,obviously I'm now out of control.

509
00:32:17,625 --> 00:32:19,865
至于你信不信，我反正信了，当时我就是失去控制了
Believe it or not,I'm now out of control.

510
00:32:20,945 --> 00:32:24,984
就像飚车的年轻人那样，那时我已经失去了对车的控制
As arrogant as us boys are,I have now lost control of that car.

511
00:32:24,985 --> 00:32:29,504
就是这么回事。你当时还踩着刹车吗？
That's gone. Do you find yourself in a situation like that braking?

512
00:32:29,505 --> 00:32:32,705
刹车灯还亮着，大概，没错
The brakelights will still be on, probably, yes.

513
00:32:33,905 --> 00:32:36,144
为什么还不减速？
"Why isn't it slowing down?"

514
00:32:36,145 --> 00:32:39,664
之后还有一次，当然，是在F1里的那次碰撞
And then, of course, that was the big Formula 1 airborne one.

515
00:32:39,665 --> 00:32:42,264
是在瓦伦西亚吗？是的。那是一次很严重的撞车
Was that Valencia? Yeah.It was quite a big crash.

516
00:32:42,265 --> 00:32:43,704
我们有段录像
We've got the footage here,

517
00:32:43,705 --> 00:32:47,505
给各位重温一下韦伯的那段经历，你人生中最刺激的一刻，是的
just to remind everybody of Mark,one of your finest hours, really.

518
00:32:57,945 --> 00:32:59,544
又看了一遍，我觉得...
Again, I find myself...

519
00:32:59,545 --> 00:33:01,784
当时那一瞬间你大脑里都在想些什么
What does go through your mind apart from,

520
00:33:01,785 --> 00:33:04,544
哇噢，那就像坐游乐场里的过山车一样？
"Wow, it's like a fairground ride"?

521
00:33:04,545 --> 00:33:08,464
你只是需要离莲花赛车远一点，伙计，这就是你需要做的
You've just got to stay away from Lotuses mate,that's the long and short of it.

522
00:33:08,465 --> 00:33:10,864
通过这两场事故
The thing about both of those accidents,

523
00:33:10,865 --> 00:33:13,904
我认为首先，你一定受到了一点...
I think the first one,you suffered a little bit of...

524
00:33:13,905 --> 00:33:16,464
我有些脑震荡，脖子也有点伤
I had some concussion, neck problems.

525
00:33:16,465 --> 00:33:20,224
是那次吗，那次F1的撞车？我很走运
That one, though, the one in the Formula 1 car? I was lucky.

526
00:33:20,225 --> 00:33:22,704
我踩断了制动踏板,实际上。这就是当时发生的事情
I snapped the brake pedal,actually. So that was about it.

527
00:33:22,705 --> 00:33:25,024
通常我们不在那里踩刹车
Which is unusual to do from that side.

528
00:33:25,025 --> 00:33:27,504
需要很大的力量，和勇气
A lot of power required, adrenaline.

529
00:33:27,505 --> 00:33:30,544
你实际上还踩坏了你的...？断了。突然断裂
You actually broke it with your own...? Snapped it. Just popped it.

530
00:33:30,545 --> 00:33:33,544
什么，你用脚踩断了刹车？是的
What, just with the force of your own foot? Exactly.

531
00:33:33,545 --> 00:33:36,464
所以你从这两场事故中一路走来，令人印象深刻
So you walk away from both those accidents, which is remarkable,

532
00:33:36,465 --> 00:33:39,504
2008年开始你还参加自行车比赛
and yet you go cycling in 2008,

533
00:33:39,505 --> 00:33:44,664
撞到一辆日产都灵，我记得。那辆日产赢了，伙计，日产赢了
bump into a Nissan Torino,I believe. It won, mate, it won.

534
00:33:44,665 --> 00:33:47,624
日产赢了。你撞断了你的腿？
It won. And you broke your leg?

535
00:33:47,625 --> 00:33:49,144
是的。和肩膀...
Yeah. Shoulder...

536
00:33:49,145 --> 00:33:53,744
因为这是一个教育孩子们的好案例
Because this is what I think we need to impress upon children watching.

537
00:33:53,745 --> 00:33:56,545
不要骑自行车。因为它们很危险
Don't get a bicycle.Because they're dangerous.

538
00:33:57,985 --> 00:34:02,145
现在，很显然，就像我们在介绍中说的那样，你已经确认不再参加明年的F1比赛
Now obviously, you've, as we said in the introduction, handed notice in.

539
00:34:04,825 --> 00:34:07,944
为什么？你要去哪？你将要做些什么？
Why? Where are you going?What you going to do?

540
00:34:07,945 --> 00:34:09,824
如今这个时间正适合我，伙计
Timing's right for me, mate.

541
00:34:09,825 --> 00:34:13,784
对于已经参加14年F1比赛的我来说，是时候调整一下了
Bit of a break from what I've been doing for the last 14 years.

542
00:34:13,785 --> 00:34:16,664
我明年就去保时捷车队跑勒芒了，事实上
So I'm going to race with Porsche, actually.

543
00:34:16,665 --> 00:34:18,784
我知道你一直很喜欢保时捷，对吧？
I know you love Porsches, don't you?

544
00:34:18,785 --> 00:34:20,985
911是部好车！
The 911 is such an interesting car!

545
00:34:23,105 --> 00:34:26,704
不，让我疑虑的是，你真觉得现在是你离开F1的最佳时机吗？
No, cos what worries me,do you think you're getting out at the right time of Formula 1?

546
00:34:26,705 --> 00:34:29,224
如今F1有了不稳定的轮胎
Now that we've got the tyres going off like they do,

547
00:34:29,225 --> 00:34:30,904
这是不是使得比赛变得乏味了？
is that getting a bit wearisome?

548
00:34:30,905 --> 00:34:33,464
你坐进赛车，赛车很棒，你也了解赛道
You're in the car, the car's going well, you know the track,

549
00:34:33,465 --> 00:34:36,544
你在最佳的状态，并且你知道如果你全力驾驶的话
you're in the groove and you know that if you push hard,

550
00:34:36,545 --> 00:34:39,224
你的轮胎会快速衰竭这样你就赢不了比赛了
your tyres will simply wear out and you can't win.

551
00:34:39,225 --> 00:34:42,544
这很不同，伙计，和以前比较起来
It is very different, mate,from how it used to be.

552
00:34:42,545 --> 00:34:45,944
但现实就是如此，所以我们要不断学习并掌握它
But that's the way it is, we've got to learn and get on with it.

553
00:34:45,945 --> 00:34:49,104
你在F1里要学会进步
But you've got to be able to push.In Formula 1,

554
00:34:49,105 --> 00:34:53,184
全心全意地投入其中.就应该这样
it's about us boys absolutely on the limits all the time. It should be.

555
00:34:53,185 --> 00:34:55,544
明年F1规则会有大改变
There's a big regulation change next year.

556
00:34:55,545 --> 00:34:59,824
赛车会变得更加省油。1.6升排量的引擎？
We're going to have to save fuel.1.6 litre engines?

557
00:34:59,825 --> 00:35:03,744
我想说我的福特科蒂娜也是1.6升的排气量
I mean, my Ford Cortina had a 1.6 litre engine.

558
00:35:03,745 --> 00:35:06,265
所以你会想念你的队友吗？
So are you going to miss your team-mate?

559
00:35:14,025 --> 00:35:15,985
我会不会想念维特尔？
Am I going to miss Seb?

560
00:35:17,505 --> 00:35:21,504
大概不会太想他，不会
Probably not a huge amount, no.

561
00:35:21,505 --> 00:35:24,744
在一个竞争的环境里，总有一点点不和谐的气氛
In a competitive environment, there's always going to be a bit of needle.

562
00:35:24,745 --> 00:35:28,584
我们之间有很多恩怨，显然，但那都是过去时了
There's a lot of history between us two, obviously, that's gone before.

563
00:35:28,585 --> 00:35:33,345
是不是从今年马来西亚站开始他就变得不太听话了？
Did it start in Malaysia when he suddenly lost the ability to hear?

564
00:35:34,905 --> 00:35:37,784
车队对他说“不要超过韦伯”
It was basically "Don't overtake Mark",

565
00:35:37,785 --> 00:35:41,464
他听到了除了“不要”之外的每一个字
and then he heard everything apart from the "don't".

566
00:35:41,465 --> 00:35:45,185
我想说，你是个澳洲人。你是否曾经有过一种冲动想要...?
I mean, you're an Aussie.Have you never felt tempted to...?

567
00:35:47,025 --> 00:35:49,624
这是为了报我那一箭之仇
"This is for Gallipoli, blam!"

568
00:35:49,625 --> 00:35:53,104
很多人都说是的。我有些不安了
A lot of people are saying yes.I'm a bit concerned.

569
00:35:53,105 --> 00:35:56,345
我老爸曾经教导我“不要欺负小朋友”，所以...
My dad always says,"You shouldn't hit boys, mate", so...

570
00:36:00,025 --> 00:36:01,065
说得好
